  "prompt": "How do I deal with not being good enough for my parents?",
  "response": "Dealing with feelings of not being good enough for your parents can be challenging. Here are some helpful strategies:\n\n1. Communicate openly\n- Talk to your parents about how you feel\n- Express your emotions and concerns\n- Listen to their perspective\n\n2. Recognize your own worth\n- Your value is not determined by your parents' expectations\n- Develop self-confidence and self-acceptance\n- Focus on your personal growth and achievements\n\n3. Set realistic expectations\n- Understand that no one is perfect\n- Learn to distinguish between realistic and unrealistic expectations\n- Set achievable personal goals\n\n4. Seek support\n- Talk to a trusted friend or counselor\n- Consider therapy to work through feelings of inadequacy\n- Join support groups with similar experiences\n\n5. Practice self-compassion\n- Be kind to yourself\n- Acknowledge your efforts and progress\n- Treat yourself with the same understanding you'd offer a friend\n\n6. Establish boundaries\n- Learn to say no when expectations feel overwhelming\n- Communicate your limits clearly\n- Prioritize your mental health\n\n7. Develop your own identity\n- Pursue your passions and interests\n- Build a life that makes you happy\n- Remember that your path may differ from your parents' expectations\n\nRemember, your worth is not defined by your parents' approval.",
